Coercive Power Tactics: Threatening or using force to control people. Punishment, intimidation, and threats. Reward Power Tactics: Using prizes or incentives to persuade people. Promotions, bonuses, and incentives. Legitimate Power Tactics: Using official authority or position power to influence others. Delegating, ordering, and deciding are examples. Expert Power Strategies: These tactics employ expertise to persuade others. Provide information, recommendations, and professional views. Referent Power Tactics: Charm, charisma, and likability are used to influence people. Networking, trust, and relationships are examples. Informational Power Tactics: Using facts to persuade others. Statistics, proof, and facts are examples. Power techniques may be moral or unethical depending on the situation and how they're used. 